摘 要    談到中國大陸公民社會的發展，無疑地即是在表述國家與社會關係的變遷。本文認為：不論是中共政府自身體認到黨政體制有其改革的迫切需要，抑或是因市場經濟力量的興起，而被動改革因應，中共的「經改」與「政改」都已經是不得不然，也必須要如此做，才能和迅速崛起的民間社會力量相適應。而民間力量表現得最為顯著的特徵，即是公民社會多元文化的呈現，這些新興的自主性領域與社會力量，構成了目前中國公民社會的面貌。不論是民間組織的興起、中產階級的壯大、公共領域的發展，都引領著國家與社會關係的變革。而公民社會的發展也必須要有民主的權力與法治的社會作為基礎。    現階段中國的公民社會還處於一個萌芽的初始階段，在中共的統治下，它是一種典型政府主導的公民社會型態，具有明顯的官民雙重性與過渡性，表現出不同於西方社會的特點。而新生的民間社會也大多選擇和政府「合作」，而非「對抗」的模式，以謀求自身和國家最大的利益。在政府和民間社會有交集的情況下，由過去強調國家的絕對「統治」，轉向以「治理」體制來理順國家與社會（特別是公民社會）之關係，變得更有其正當性與迫切的需要。    將來中國大陸可以在市場經濟的成長之下，以「市場」為觸媒，一方面國家透過市場放權、還權於社會，另一方面社會在市場的培育下，以不挑戰黨國的權威為前提，行使對國家的監督與制衡權利，並彌補國家職能有所不足的部分。而國家權力在充分的遵行法制下，解決市場失效所不能解決的問題，並對社會成員及公民社會的合法權利提供保障，從而在國家與社會之間形成一種動態平衡。在這個過程中，國家是否能透過和公民社會彼此的協商、合作互助，建立伙伴關係、遊戲規則與網絡化管理，以期達到雙贏的目標，則是值得進一步觀察的重點。

Abstract  Mention about the development of Civil Society in Mainland China, it is no doubt referring to the change of relationship between state and society. The statement of this thesis is：No matter whether Chinese government realizes that the reform on the structure of its party and politics is urgent, or it is forced to proceed on the reform by the emerging of market economy, Chinese government has to keep the path of “Economic Reform” and “Political Reform” to match the rapidly growing strength of Civil Society. The most outstanding characteristic of the social strength is the presentation of multiple cultures by the Civil Society. The emerging independent field and the social strength constitute the display of current Civil Society in China. The upsurge of civil organizations, growth of the middle class, and the developing of public field all lead to the reform of the relationship between state and society. The development of Civil Society should be based on a society with democratic power and the rule by law.  The Civil Society in today’s China is still in its early stage which, under the governance by the Chinese Communist Party, is the stereotype of the Government-oriented Civil Society whose apparent characteristics of government-civil dual natures and the transition are different from that in the Western society. Most of the emerging civil organizations choose to be “cooperating” instead of “confronting” with the government which can actually lead to the utmost benefit for the state and for oneself. Under the consensus reached between the state and the civil organizations, it is becoming more reasonable that the previous absolute “dominating” situation by the government has been changed to “administrating” structure to meet the relationship between the state and the society (esp. the Civil Society.)  In China, the booming of market economy can take the “market” as the accelerant to ensure the empowering to the society in one way, and to enable the society to implement the right of auditing or counterbalancing the state in another. The power of the state, under the obedience to the law, can solve the problems which the market’s ineffectiveness has left behind. This will provide the protection to the members of the society as well as to the legal right for the Civil Society which in return crates a “Dynamic Equilibrium” between the state and society. During this process, it worth of our close watch to check whether the state can build up the partnership, game rules and the network management through mutual negotiation and cooperation with the Civil Society for achieving the win-win target.

